Pregnancy can bring about various physical transformations, and each woman experiences these changes differently. These transformations may affect a woman's self-image and comfort with her body.

Pregnancy not only brings physical changes but also triggers emotional, psychological, and social transformations. The anticipation of motherhood can cause stress and raise numerous questions for some women.
Pregnancy can cause women to experience a range of conflicting emotions, such as joy, worry, denial, excitement, and even sadness.
Discussing your emotions with loved ones or other pregnant women can provide valuable support and help normalize the experience.
